sightings.log: I saw it. I know I did. People say I was overreacting.  They say it was a cat or raccoon. Really?! What kind of creature would you find in a rural grocery store lot with appendages that could clasp a can like that?  I saw it slink away from the delivery truck as the moonlight danced on it's slender body.  There seemed to be a strange wispiness as though it's skin was made of shimmery silver scales that sprouted thin strands of long silk black hair.  I swear it!

It sat up on it's haunches.  'Looked like it had a pouch.  As if it had some sort of front facing fannie pack, it reached torward it's chest and grabbed a can of soup from somewhere within.  It commenced to knaw on it.  Such a ponderous creature. Why such a hankerin for soup?
sightings.logLocation: Bout 30 miles northwest of mile marker 11, past the berry patch on the right.
